difficulty_engine - “How hard should TODAY’s workout be?”

    “The Difficulty Engine dynamically adapts workout intensity using user behavior, fatigue estimation, and energy feedback to ensure sustainable fitness progression.”

        The Difficulty Engine is the core decision-making module of the AI system.
        it analyses based on
            - past workout behaviour
            - user fatigue
            - consistency
            - today's energy level
        This ensures workouts are adaptive, sustainable, and dropout-aware.

adapt_difficulty(ai_state, workout_history, energy_level)

Inputs
ai_state (dict)
Persistent AI memory stored later in PostgreSQL JSONB.
Tracks long-term behavioral signals

workout_history (list[dict])
Ground-truth workout records from past days.

energy_level (str)
User-reported daily energy level:
"low" | "medium" | "high"

🔹 Internal Logic Breakdown
1️⃣ Consistency Calculation
Measures how often the user completes workouts.
Used to decide progression or regression.
Logic
consistency = completed_sessions / total_sessions
Special case
New users → default consistency = 0.5 (neutral)

2️⃣ Fatigue Score Estimation
Prevents overtraining and burnout.
Computed using the last 3 completed workouts.

Rules
Completed high-intensity workout → +0.3
Completed medium/low workout → +0.2
Fatigue capped at 1.0

3️⃣ Skip Detection (Dropout Risk)
Counts skipped workouts in the last 5 sessions.
Used to reduce difficulty instead of punishing the user.

4️⃣ Difficulty Decision Rules
Difficulty is chosen using explainable rule-based logic:

Condition	Decision
≥2 skipped workouts	Difficulty → low, skip risk → high
High consistency (≥80%) & low fatigue	Difficulty → high
High fatigue or low energy	Difficulty → low
Otherwise	Difficulty → medium
5️⃣ AI State Update
The engine updates and persists:
current_difficulty
fatigue_score
consistency_score
skip_risk
This state is reused for future decisions.

🔹 Why Rule-Based (Not ML)
Works reliably with small data
Fully explainable
Fast execution
Prevents unsafe decisions
Can be upgraded to ML later

