WORKOUT_GENERATOR

“The Workout Generator converts adaptive difficulty decisions into safe, time-bounded, and energy-aware workout plans using rule-based templates.”


The Workout Generator is responsible for creating the actual workout plan for the user, based on:

the difficulty decided by the Difficulty Engine

the user’s available time

current energy level

workout location (home or gym)

This module transforms AI decisions into executable workouts.

Inputs to the Generator
difficulty (str)

Determined by the Difficulty Engine:

"low"

"medium"

"high"

Controls workout intensity (sets, reps, rest).

available_time (int)

User’s available workout time in minutes.

Used to:

limit number of exercises

keep workouts short and achievable

energy_level (str)

User-reported daily energy:

"low"

"medium"

"high"

Used to scale intensity down on low-energy days.

location (str)

Workout location:

"home" (default)

"gym"

Used to select safe exercise templates.

Internal Components & Logic
1️⃣ Exercise Templates

Predefined, safe exercise lists for different environments.

Home Workouts

Warm-up: light mobility

Main: bodyweight exercises

Cooldown: stretching and breathing

Gym Workouts

Warm-up: cardio + mobility

Main: machine-based strength

Cooldown: stretching / recovery

Reason:
Ensures safety, consistency, and easy expansion.

2️⃣ Difficulty-to-Intensity Mapping

Each difficulty level maps to measurable intensity parameters.

Difficulty	Sets	Reps	Rest (sec)
Low	1	8	60
Medium	2	12	45
High	3	15	30

Reason:
Makes “difficulty” concrete and explainable.

3️⃣ Energy-Based Scaling

On "low" energy days:

Reps are reduced

Sets are reduced

Minimum thresholds enforced

Effect:
Prevents burnout while maintaining consistency.

4️⃣ Time-Aware Exercise Selection

One main exercise ≈ 5 minutes

Number of main exercises = available_time // 5

Minimum of one exercise enforced

Effect:
Workouts always fit within real-life time constraints.

5️⃣ Structured Workout Assembly

The generator:

Selects warm-up exercises

Builds main workout with sets/reps/rest

Adds cooldown activities

Returns a clean, frontend-ready structure

Role in the AI System

This module:

Consumes output from the Difficulty Engine

Produces visible, actionable workouts

Feeds context into AI Coach explanations

Impacts weekly reports and pattern analysis

🔹 Why Not ML / GenAI Here

Workout safety requires determinism

Templates avoid unsafe exercise generation

GenAI will be layered later for phrasing and variation

