Pattern Analysis

🔹 Purpose

The Pattern Analysis module is the learning layer of the AI system.
It analyzes historical workout behavior to detect long-term patterns and updates the AI’s internal memory (ai_state) accordingly.

Unlike workout generation, this module does not create workouts.
It observes behavior and learns from it.

🔹 Inputs
workout_history (list[dict])

A chronological list of past workouts.

Each entry contains:

{
  "completed": true,
  "difficulty": "medium"
}


This data represents ground-truth user behavior.

ai_state (dict)

Persistent AI memory (stored later as PostgreSQL JSONB).

Example before update:

{}

🔹 Output

Returns the updated AI state with newly learned behavioral insights.

Example output:

{
  "completion_rate": 0.67,
  "difficulty_success_rate": {
    "low": 1.0,
    "medium": 0.5,
    "high": 0.0
  },
  "skip_risk": "medium",
  "trend": "improving",
  "preferred_difficulty": "low"
}

🔹 Internal Logic & Signals Extracted
1️⃣ Completion Rate

Measures overall workout adherence.

Logic

completion_rate = completed_sessions / total_sessions


Why it matters

Indicates discipline and habit formation

Feeds difficulty adaptation and reporting

2️⃣ Difficulty-wise Success Rate

Analyzes how well the user performs at each difficulty level.

Logic

Group workouts by difficulty

Compute completion rate per group

Why it matters

Prevents pushing users beyond their sustainable level

Identifies what difficulty works best

3️⃣ Skip Risk Detection

Detects recent skipping behavior using the last 5 workouts.

Skips	Risk
≥ 3	High
2	Medium
≤ 1	Low

Why it matters

Enables proactive difficulty reduction

Helps prevent dropout

4️⃣ Trend Analysis (Progress Direction)

Compares older vs recent workout performance.

Logic

Split history into two halves

Compare completion rates

Possible trends

improving

declining

stable

Why it matters

Guides coaching tone

Improves weekly insights

5️⃣ Preferred Difficulty Detection

Identifies the difficulty level with the highest success rate.

Logic

preferred_difficulty = argmax(difficulty_success_rate)


Why it matters

Personalizes future workouts

Enables AI-driven recommendations

🔹 Design Characteristics

✔ Lightweight learning (no heavy ML)
✔ Fully explainable
✔ Data-efficient
✔ Behavior-aware
✔ Safe for small datasets

🔹 Role in Overall AI System

This module:

Enhances the Difficulty Engine’s decisions

Informs Workout Generator personalization

Feeds AI Coach explanations

Powers Weekly Fitness Reports

🔹 Why This Is Not Deep Learning

Dataset is small and evolving

Behavioral transparency is required

Rule-based learning is safer and faster

ML upgrade path remains open

🔹 One-Line Summary (PPT Ready)

“Pattern Analysis learns user behavior trends from workout history to personalize difficulty and prevent dropout.”

