weekly report

Purpose

The Weekly Fitness Report module generates a human-readable summary of the user’s weekly activity.
It converts raw workout data and learned AI insights into actionable feedback.

This module answers:

“How did the user perform this week and what should they focus on next?”

🔹 Inputs
workout_history (list[dict])

Chronological list of workouts.

Each entry includes:

{
  "completed": true,
  "difficulty": "low"
}


This data represents actual user behavior.

ai_state (dict)

AI’s learned memory from previous modules (Pattern Analysis).

Typical fields used:

{
  "trend": "improving",
  "preferred_difficulty": "low",
  "skip_risk": "medium"
}

🔹 Output

Returns a structured weekly summary:

{
  "summary": "You completed 4 out of 6 workouts this week.",
  "consistency": "66%",
  "trend": "improving",
  "insight": "Your consistency is improving. Keep building momentum.",
  "suggestion": "Low-intensity workouts work best for you right now."
}


This output is directly consumable by the frontend.

🔹 Internal Logic & Breakdown
1️⃣ Empty History Handling

If no workouts exist:

Returns a friendly onboarding message

Encourages short, achievable workouts

Why

Prevents blank screens

Improves user experience for new users

2️⃣ Weekly Window Selection

Only the last 7 workouts are considered.

Logic

last_week = workout_history[-7:]


Why

Focuses on recent behavior

Prevents outdated patterns from influencing feedback

3️⃣ Consistency Calculation

Measures adherence for the week.

Logic

consistency = completed / total


Converted into percentage for readability.

4️⃣ Trend Awareness

Uses the trend signal from Pattern Analysis:

improving

declining

stable

Why

Aligns messaging tone with user progress

Avoids generic feedback

5️⃣ Insight Generation

Generates a motivational insight based on trend.

Trend	Insight
Improving	Positive reinforcement
Declining	Gentle corrective feedback
Stable	Neutral encouragement
6️⃣ Personalized Suggestion

Combines:

skip risk

preferred difficulty

To suggest what the user should do next.

Examples

High skip risk → shorter workouts

Low preferred difficulty → lighter routines

High preferred difficulty → safe progression

🔹 Design Characteristics

✔ Human-centric messaging
✔ Fully explainable
✔ Behavior-aware
✔ Uses learned AI state
✔ Frontend-ready JSON output

🔹 Role in the Overall AI System

This module:

Consolidates outputs from all AI components

Acts as the final feedback layer

Improves user motivation and retention

Strengthens demo and presentation impact

🔹 Why This Is Rule-Based

Reports require clarity, not prediction

Deterministic insights build trust

Lightweight logic ensures consistency

🔹 One-Line Summary (PPT Ready)

“The Weekly Report transforms behavioral data into clear insights and personalized guidance to help users stay consistent.”

